This paper is about semantic role labeling, which is a task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses deep neural network-based approaches, which suggests that it could be relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper investigates the use of syntax-aware representations, which could be relevant to categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as these fields often deal with structured data.
